{
  "thig5.4:0.1": "Verses of the Senior Nuns 5.4 ",
  "thig5.4:0.2": "The Book of the Fives ",
  "thig5.4:0.3": "Sundarīnandā ",
  "thig5.4:1.1": "“Nandā, see this bag of bones as ",
  "thig5.4:1.2": "diseased, filthy, and rotten. ",
  "thig5.4:1.3": "With mind unified and serene, ",
  "thig5.4:1.4": "meditate on the ugly aspects of the body: ",
  "thig5.4:2.1": "as this is, so is that, ",
  "thig5.4:2.2": "as that is, so is this. ",
  "thig5.4:2.3": "A foul stink wafts from it, ",
  "thig5.4:2.4": "it is the fools’ delight.” ",
  "thig5.4:3.1": "Reflecting in such a way, ",
  "thig5.4:3.2": "tireless all day and night, ",
  "thig5.4:3.3": "having broken through ",
  "thig5.4:3.4": "with my own wisdom, I saw. ",
  "thig5.4:4.1": "Being diligent, ",
  "thig5.4:4.2": "rationally investigating, ",
  "thig5.4:4.3": "I truly saw this body ",
  "thig5.4:4.4": "both inside and out. ",
  "thig5.4:5.1": "Then, growing disillusioned with the body, ",
  "thig5.4:5.2": "I became dispassionate within. ",
  "thig5.4:5.3": "Diligent, detached, ",
  "thig5.4:5.4": "I’m quenched and at peace. "
}